### device_info Method
```rust
fn device_info(&self, info: &DeviceInfo) {
    // Build specification table
    let mut table = Table::new()
        .with_column(Column::new("").style(self.theme.label.clone()))
        .with_column(Column::new("").style(self.theme.value.clone()))
        .box_style(&BoxChars::ROUNDED);

    table.add_row_cells(["Serial", &info.serial]);
    table.add_row_cells(["Firmware", &info.firmware_version]);
    table.add_row_cells(["Keys", &format!("{} ({} columns × {} rows)", 
        info.key_count, info.cols, info.rows)]);
    table.add_row_cells(["Key Size", &format!("{}×{} pixels", 
        info.key_width, info.key_height)]);
    table.add_row_cells(["Device Type", &info.kind]);

    // Render table to segments
    let table_segments = table.render(self.width().saturating_sub(6));

    // Build key layout
    let key_layout = self.render_key_layout(info.rows, info.cols);

    // Combine into content
    let mut content = Text::new("");
    content.append("\n");

    // Add table (need to convert segments to text)
    for segment in table_segments {
        content.append(&segment.text);
    }

    content.append("\n");
    content.append_styled("  Key Layout:\n", self.theme.label.clone());
    content.append(&key_layout);

    let panel = Panel::from_rich_text(content, self.width().saturating_sub(4))
        .title(&info.product_name)
        .border_style(Style::new().color(self.theme.accent.clone()))
        .rounded();

    self.console.print_renderable(&panel);
}
```

## Design Decisions

### Table for Specifications
- Key-value pairs are perfect for table layout
- Labels in left column, values in right
- Consistent alignment improves scannability

### Key Layout Grid
- ASCII art provides immediate visual understanding
- Shows key numbering convention (left-to-right, top-to-bottom)
- Essential for users setting up key configurations
- Uses box-drawing characters that match panel style

### Panel Title
- Uses device product name (e.g., "Stream Deck XL")
- Centered in panel header for prominence

### Information Selection
- Serial: Needed for multi-device scenarios
- Firmware: Useful for troubleshooting
- Keys: Count and layout dimensions
- Key Size: Important for image preparation
- Device Type: Internal identifier

## Edge Cases
- Stream Deck Mini (6 keys, 3×2): Smaller grid
- Stream Deck Original (15 keys, 5×3): Medium grid
- Stream Deck XL (32 keys, 8×4): Full grid as shown
- Stream Deck + (8 keys, 4×2): Narrow grid

